@NODE "Introduction" "Introduction"
@{b}Introduction:@{ub}

Have you ever seen a user just pressing return for no reason?
Well in that case you probably wonder why?
I did to... So i made a program that sends fun comments if the user
just press return or types unknown commands.

AND if the user do this alot he will enter a list...
Alist of Most Stupid Users! :-)
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Installation" "Installation"
@{b}Installation:@{ub}

Copy all files in the archive somewere in Pfiles config programs
as you want... 

*** Remember to Config ALL Rexx programs!! ***

Input this to in the beginning of the folowign lines in  the BBSText. 

#0Ram:rtp/ReturnPrg.rexx}

68 FIRST
394 FIRST
397 FIRST
663 FIRST
672 FIRST
673 FIRST
674 FIRST
1531 FIRST

And line 1610 shold lock like this:
n1q0c6#0Ram:rtp/ReturnPrg.rexx}BBSList> q1

Insert this in line 99:
#0ram:Rtp/SaveHig.Rexx}

Replace line 311 whit the folowing line
#0Ram:RTP/UnknownCommand.Rexx}

Now insert this commad in your BBSMenu:
STUpid			`0- |#0Ram:RTP/ReturnProgShowHig.Rexx}

Well, thats the beginning...
Now write this in your User-Startup or where ever in your startup...

Makedir Ram:RTP
Copy PFiles:RTP/ RAM:RTP All Quiet
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Requirements" "Requirements"
@{b}Requirements:@{ub}

CNET BBS v3.05 by Perspective Software.
Rexx running. :-)
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Usage" "Usage"
@{b}Usage:@{ub}

Just logon and press return, return, return, return, return...
Use command STUpid to chek out the list...
@ENDNODE

